P5oyxYkSGrV8YyZ2MVowdUGBvrPnGN6bVnQqPFunaKK6o_WP4E4mx8mSTbFh-zzj9dB00z6URvHQYPDeVnkrK67acR4_MmaIfWanWCQzWkE4W3Z3JAr-wA1aUKS_y4p6LB_E6-FUjqniPSvSjr89I4eZYo6SinfHBIEki92RA8Ch472GoU6yAc7hZJuKyA4JbDKfkkzVRp1tk2Qb00REiOicgSi4QDao_X7ucTtDlXBDvUKbT7p2BNGRThe0GBrnWIemyTpRe7b8CwNvAubieseTyli5VSpKPjxdGVeFTr41ZhadJJK9vOY565DL8EOvRp0hJ2mRgDL-ufI3Obc1pHWl8kwoNHxw2gC7eTAhy8FAHgOrqd-iYGpjvzZF8Gbe6kIJwYlrV5a7cfEycIJf2iO6a1kBnrMBqtWMxd42IEFffAC9BncnsY2K8FnBXWYwq524g-W64XQ0RVeCB6KYdHzdFvW_00rG-rF5rt-6dG-PvU6wfFr_fSNPW0OyshygZ3szDkiG_0msaKhVfwnxCJg9935N-eQnxd5987Z6Qvydm3WY9PazEgvgX4MNOBc59rgou8nJFOSFzrauI-Q==\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring method invocation**\\n\\nI'm considering whether we need to make sure the closure is properly loaded and initialized before calling class$. I wonder if using `MethodHandle` could be clearer than reflection since it might avoid some direct invocation issues. However, Class.forName might still encounter similar problems. \\n\\nMaybe invoking `org.codehaus.groovy.runtime.InvokerHelper.invokeStaticMethod` could work since it uses public methods. But, it still feels reflective. I also think about writing a Java helper in a package outside of the library or including a Groovy test source, but there seem to be limitations.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Revising the approach to closures**\\n\\nIt seems we should probably avoid using direct `class$` references and instead focus on capturing the closure and invoking `closure.getProperty(\\\"contentType\\\")`. I wonder if `javap` shows that GroovyObject uses metaClass to call a generated getter like `getContentType`, which differs from using Class.forName.\\n\\nHowever, since the call site is class$, perhaps the `class$` helper could be useful for `getContentType` when targeting Java 1.4. But it's puzzling that `javap` can use a class literal for Matcher. Maybe I should leave an explanation while also focusing on the necessary code changes? Analyzing source closure14 maps to contentType(Matcher) against our public API might be a way to improve this.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_uMtvZQRzG6TaBqtPussPVSsN|fc_0aa34280b7ba4278016a27c3a8b60481968b705159fa0eddbd", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/io.rest-assured/rest-assured/5.5.0/user-code-filter.json", "limit": 120}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1163, "output": 884, "cacheRead": 58368, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 60415, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1780990863267, "responseId": "resp_0aa34280b7ba4278016a27c38fdd00819690591ef30b3800b5"}}
